<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?>
<!--
  Static sitemap for the accessibility-scanner practice site.

  DO NOT RENAME THIS FILE TO sitemap.xml — the extensionless name is
  deliberate and load-bearing.

  The BlinkPages edge answers /sitemap*.xml itself, before static assets ever
  resolve, and returns a hard 404. It matches, case-insensitively:

      /^\/sitemap(?:[-_][\w-]+)?\.xml$/i

  so sitemap.xml, sitemap_index.xml, sitemap-index.xml and sitemap-0.xml are
  all unreachable — a file at any of those names is served to nobody. (This is
  a non-production staging guard, which also synthesizes a "Disallow: /"
  robots.txt and an X-Robots-Tag: noindex header. It lifts when the tenant's
  production hostname resolves; see the apex/DNS note below. Reference
  implementation of the same worker template: blinkmetrics.com/src/worker.js.)

  The regex requires a .xml extension, and AAArdvark's DetectSitemap probes
  three paths in order — sitemap.xml, sitemap_index.xml, sitemap — so the third,
  extensionless probe is the one that escapes the guard. DetectSitemap gates only
  on an HTTP 200 plus a successful XML parse and never inspects Content-Type,
  so serving XML from an extensionless path is fine.

  Deliberately hand-maintained rather than generated by @astrojs/sitemap:
    * The integration emits sitemap-index.xml / sitemap-0.xml. AAArdvark's
      DetectSitemap job only probes sitemap.xml, sitemap_index.xml and sitemap,
      so the integration's output would never be discovered.
    * The integration derives URLs from `site` in astro.config.mjs, which is the
      tenant canonical host (a11y-practice-pluto.blinkpages.site). The scanner
      tests address this site as https://www.discoverpluto.site, and the sitemap
      URLs must match the site's base_url for the "add pages from sitemap" flow.

  Note the apex (https://discoverpluto.site) is NOT usable: DNS is at Hover and
  the apex A record points at Hover's URL forwarder, which does not support
  HTTPS. Always use the www host here.

  Maintenance: if you add or remove a page in src/pages/, update this file too
  (same rule as ISSUES.md). Routes use Astro's default directory build format,
  so every path carries a trailing slash.
-->
<urlset xmlns="http://www.sitemaps.org/schemas/sitemap/0.9">
  <url><loc>https://www.discoverpluto.site/</loc></url>
  <url><loc>https://www.discoverpluto.site/about/</loc></url>
